The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in West Sussex so far as at 07 March is 231,368 (26,666.5 cases per 100,000 population). In the seven days to 02 March, there were 4,098 new confirmed cases (472.3 new cases per 100,000). In the seven days to 23 February, there were 4,737 new cases, and so the new cases have decreased by 13% (639 fewer cases).
